Hiya all,<br>
     This is my first post on this site, i've been reading the comments on Wizards turning into taxis and the class balancing issues. and i have come across another flaw in Verants logic. Now i hope this is the right board to place this on and i apologise if its been said before but if as Verant says Transportation is &quot;a specialty of wizards&quot; why is it that Wizards don't get the West Commons portal until 39th.. when druids get it at 29th...<br>
    I play on Cazic Thule and by far the most wanted destination is FP/WC which means at least to me that Druids are you most popular Taxi Service from 29th upwards... And that whilst wizards are slogging their way through to 39th (relying on a Guildmate getting me a space in his group mainly) the druids get all the port donations, and always have cash to buy their next set of spells...<br>
<br>
   Basically i think if Verant is really serious perhaps they should lower WC portal in level.. otherwise it sounds to me like an attempt to appease wizards without giving us anything real.<br>
<br>
<br>
Galear Flamingsoul<br>
26th Wizard<br>
Cazic Thule<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umandari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/24/01 10:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards as Taxi's</span><hr size=1> Verant's position on wizards as &quot;Masters of Travel&quot; is not based on the locations of our ports or the levels at which we get them, but on our Translocates.  Prior to these spells we shared the Masters of Travel distinction with druids.  With Velious, Verant is attempting to grant wizards the top spot in this area.  I believe that they hope these additions will also ameliorate our feelings regarding the Cazic port, Skyshrine evac, location of WK port, etc.<br>
Still, comparing wizard porting to druid porting is like comparing Valu-Jet to Concorde.  With Translocates we're getting more transport capabilities, but druids have the fine destinations.<br>
<br>
Caracatan Stormforge<br>
Devotee of Solusek Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umandosturambar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandos Turambar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/25/01 11:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards as Taxi's</span><hr size=1> Translocates are all pointless for us anyway; lestwise if you defined yourself as a Master of Destruction when you made your character. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uobey555.showPublicProfile?language=EN>obey555</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/31/01 1:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> Translocates may be nice, but they are low on my priority when buying my 39th lvl spells.(i.e. as in if I have money to burn!) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspace78.showPublicProfile?language=EN>space78</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/1/01 9:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards as Taxi's</span><hr size=1> now that i felt like actually logging back in and moving around with my wizard ive never had so many random tells for services. this is insane. i havent really played much since the new tl's went in, and personally i hate them, i like what they do, i hate that im being bugged with tells every 3 seconds from some stranger thinking that i should do it cuz it doesnt put me out any. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=waltzingmatilda>Waltzing Matilda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/2/01 2:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards as Taxi's</span><hr size=1> I must admit, having to wait till 39 for the WC spell isn't very helpful.<br>
<br>
I did recently write a letter to Absor over the translocate spells but thats yet to be posted ( maybe won't be? )<br>
<br>
Basically, I can see why the wizard direction with translocate spells is a natural course for us, but needs a few refinements.<br>
<br>
EG..<br>
1) New commands need to be introduced.<br>
<br>
a)  /translocate on/off ( No pop up box ) This would help with emergency translocate in group fighting.<br>
<br>
b) /translocategroup on/off ( With above, but also not requiring a person to be in a group to send ) REason for this is simple. You find youself in a group and someone wanders over wanting to be translocated. Do you, 1, remove yourself from the group, group with him, send, then regroup?. Or do you say first you have to annoy our group leader (at the time) if there is a spot group, then I can send you.<br>
<br>
I was *WAS* under the impression first that the translocates only help one person, the person being sent. But in reality it does help us not having to go ( unlike the druid ). I would prefer less mana used though :-)<br>
<br>
I find the argument from some wizzys that they are getting annnoyed for translocates now very mute. Just imagine being a druid/shaman for sows, or an enchanter for crack. Winging will result in one thing, we either loose the ability, or don't get anymore translocates. Further, most of us play other characters and therefore have to rely on someones other wizzy, so think about it. You may be in the same position one day?<br>
<br>
My second request looks like its being addressed anyway, going by the latest Al'Kabor journal #2.<br>
<br>
I find the biggest requests for ports are to the following areas and some need translocates.<br>
<br>
1) West Commons ( no spell yet)<br>
2) Dreadlands ( have it )<br>
3) Great Divide ( don't have it, looks like we may get )<br>
4) Greater fay ( have it )<br>
<br>
5-6 The plains would be  a great addition too. <br>
<br>
Of course we have a couple of others, but the above are the holiday destinations I get anyway.<br>
<br>
And some day, all us wizzys need to start a working bee and build a set of spires over at OOT :-)<br>
<br>
Waltzing Matilda ( Bristlebane )<br>
